reviewText: Interval was released in 1973. It starred Merle Oberon, and was her last film. An older woman in love with a younger man. Fans of Merle Oberon will like this the most.

A great love story with some of the best views of the Mayan ruins of Tulum and Chitzan Itza.  Ladies will enjoy watching the young drifter-artist portrayed by Robert Wolders as he falls passionately in love with a beautiful and mysterious Meryl Oberon in the wilds of the Yucatan.  Psycological suspense builds as we see glimpses of the past that dictate the mood swings of this lovely lonely lady.
  Classic Gold
